  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Integrated SGBV Response and Preventions Services for Women and Girls in Mpumalanga Province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">It is estimated that a rape happens every eight seconds in South Africa, and that one in every two women will be raped in their lifetime. Only 1 out of 36 rape cases is reported, and only 15% of those result in successful convictions. This project provides sexual and gender based violence services in Nkomazi in Mpumalanga province, a predominantly rural farming area. It provides counselling, medical and legal support to women who have experienced this violence, working to improve their confidence and empower them. It also works to change cultural practices and attitudes about the roles of men and women, and helps bring about a more responsive justice system. The project aims to reduce gender based violence, and make life better for those who have experienced it..</narrative>
  </description>
